commitResults.messageBody: This version of easyLog has an additional attribute called "price" for all items. The user is able to / has to add a price for the item to be added. The price should be a number which is between 0 and 1,000,000,000 SGD inclusive. The item list will also display the prices for different items in the system.

commitResults.messageBody: Zikun deleted a method in itemsParser class and instead reads user input in the same way as other members within a particular command class.

This version of easyLog can update the additional attribute called "price" for all items. The user is able to revise an item price any time at ease. Again, the price should be a number which is between 0 and 1,000,000,000 SGD inclusive. The item list will also display the revised prices for different items in the system.
(Zikun also adds the code base so that other fields can be updated with the same simple logic (e.g., stock).)
